                      Temple Lodging in Japan Japanese

                 Let's stay at Japanese temples and shrines!

   A shukubo is an accommodation facility that is part of a Japanese
   temple or shrine.
   Tranquility and the beautiful scenery of Japan, as well as abundant
   spiritual culture such as harmony and zen, lie within.
   A shukubo is an accommodation that lets you feel the culture and
   history of Japan, including zazen, which calms your mind, Japanese
   gardens, which show seasonal beauty and healthy shojin vegetarian
   dishes.
   We are studying how to enjoy staying at a shukubo.

